<HEAD>Idahoans Sending Potato Farming Equipment to Poland</HEAD>
<DATELINE>IDAHO FALLS, Idaho (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Idahoans are sending potato farming gear to <LOCATION> Poland </LOCATION> in a gesture of support for the democratic movement in eastern <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION>, a congressman said. About 30 pieces of equipment, including potato diggers and planters, will be sent initially, Democratic Rep. <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> Stallings </PERSON> said, noting the spud is as central to Polish agriculture as it is to farming in <LOCATION> Idaho </LOCATION>, the nation's biggest potato grower. `` We are witnessing events in <LOCATION> Eastern </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION> of historic proportions, and they started in <LOCATION> Poland </LOCATION>,'' <PERSON> Stallings </PERSON> said at a news conference Friday. `` We want to see these events succeed. `` Folks in <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> are scratching their heads trying to decide how best to respond ... In the meantime, Idahoans are moving ahead with practical solutions.'' <PERSON> Morrison </PERSON> <PERSON> Knudsen </PERSON>, a Boise-based engineering, mining and construction company, agreed to ship the equipment to the <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Coast </LOCATION>, where charitable organizations will ship it to <LOCATION> Poland </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Stallings </PERSON> said.
