 did n't work out that way. I thought we would sell more than we did,'' <PERSON> Diamond </PERSON> said in a telephone interview. Diamond estimates special interest groups paid <ORGANIZATION> Piranha </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> about $ 200,000 to hear <PERSON> Durenberger </PERSON> speak over the two-year period. <PERSON> Durenberger </PERSON> ended the contract because of the criticism he received, although the <ORGANIZATION> FEC </ORGANIZATION> concluded that payments from his publisher would constitute a stipend rather than speaking fees, he said. `` I believe I made a good faith effort to comply with the law by contacting the <ORGANIZATION> FEC </ORGANIZATION> and seeking its opinion in advance of any work I did under the agreement,'' <PERSON> Durenberger </PERSON> said in a statement his office issued recently. The complaint before the Ethics <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION> contends <PERSON> Durenberger </PERSON> misrepresented the deal to the <ORGANIZATION> FEC </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Durenberger </PERSON> lists 23 appearances in 1985 in connection with the books, including trips to <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Orleans </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Hilton </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Head </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> S.C. </LOCATION>, and four cities in <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION>. His 17 engagements in 1986 took him to <LOCATION> Palm </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Springs </LOCATION> twice and <LOCATION> Bermuda </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Monterey </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Calif. </LOCATION>, once each. <PERSON> Durenberger </PERSON> filed the amendments to his financial disclosure statements as a result of discussions between his aides and the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> Ethics Committee staff, said his press secretary, <PERSON> Carrie </PERSON> <PERSON> Collins </PERSON>. The Ethics <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION> staff has refused to comment on the investigation, but the senator's office confirmed the panel subpoena