<HEAD>PM-Obit-Sakharov, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The Soviet <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> briefly halted work on reforming the economy today to pay tribute to <PERSON> Andrei </PERSON> <PERSON> D. </PERSON> <PERSON> Sakharov </PERSON>, the colleague who was the ruling <ORGANIZATION> Communist </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION>'s most severe critic. President <PERSON> Mikhail </PERSON> <PERSON> S. </PERSON> <PERSON> Gorbachev </PERSON> and the 2,250 members of the <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> People </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Deputies </ORGANIZATION> stood for a moment of silence to remember the scientist whose challenge to the <ORGANIZATION> Kremlin </ORGANIZATION>'s human rights policies led to nearly seven years of internal exile. The 68-year-old physicist, who died Thursday night in his <LOCATION> Moscow </LOCATION> apartment, was the `` people's conscience,'' said <PERSON> Boris </PERSON> <PERSON> N. </PERSON> <PERSON> Yeltsin </PERSON>, the maverick deputy who along with <PERSON> Sakharov </PERSON> was a leader of a group considering whether to form an alternative political party. `` All honest people in the <LOCATION> U.S.S.R. </LOCATION> and throughout the world will grieve for him,'' <PERSON> Yeltsin </PERSON> said. At the time of his death, the Nobel Peace Prize winner was preparing a speech he was to give to <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> demanding that the Communists' constitutional guarantee on power be revoked, a move made by <LOCATION> Czechoslovakia </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Hungary </LOCATION> in recent weeks. In other developments in <LOCATION> Eastern </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION>: _ <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION> has established its first contacts with the <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Monetary </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Fund </OR