 that I think <PERSON> Mandela </PERSON> will go back to jail because he wo n't sit quietly and accept the system that he tried to bring down,'' she said. And she said she sees no signs of sweeping changes in <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION> along the lines of the changes in <LOCATION> Eastern </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION>. `` The biggest challenge facing <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION> is not really the removal of apartheid _ everybody already knows that apartheid is going away _ but to change the attitudes of people,'' she said. `` Getting rid of those attitudes is going to be the big problem.''
