<HEAD>Pa. Lawmaker Proposes $1 Penalty for Beating Flag Burners</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HARRISBURG, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A state lawmaker has proposed a $ 1 fine for anyone who beats up a person who burns or desecrates <LOCATION> American </LOCATION> or state flags. Rep. <PERSON> Joseph </PERSON> <PERSON> Petrarca </PERSON>, a Democrat, introduced the legislation earlier this week. The $ 1 fine would replace the normal penalties for assault or aggravated assault. A person convicted of aggravated assault could be sentenced to 10 years in jail and fined $ 25,000. <PERSON> Petrarca </PERSON> said he offered the bill because the <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> was unwilling to seek a constitutional amendment to punish flag burners. `` Since so many of our neighbors and family members have made huge sacrifices to protect it on foreign battlefields, sometimes with their lives, I feel desecrating the flag is a matter to be taken extremely seriously,'' <PERSON> Petrarca </PERSON> said in a statement. The fate of the bill is uncertain. `` I ca n't imagine this is going to go anywhere,'' Rep. <PERSON> Allen </PERSON> <PERSON> Kukovich </PERSON>, the Democrats' policy chairman, told The <ORGANIZATION> Philadelphia </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inquirer </ORGANIZATION>. `` But who knows? There are Philistines everywhere, I guess.'' <PERSON> Kukovich </PERSON> said such bills `` make the House of Representatives a laughingstock.''
