<SECOND>PM-Shearson, Bjt,0662</SECOND>
<HEAD>Struggling Brokerage Sets $900 Million Recapitalization</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By STEFAN FATSIS</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A $ 900 million recapitalization plan preserves <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lehman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hutton </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>'s credit rating at a time of weak profits and layoffs at Wall Street's second-largest brokerage. The deal, announced Thursday, also reduces parent <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Express </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>'s stake to under 50 percent and excludes investor and <ORGANIZATION> Revlon </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> Ronald </PERSON> <PERSON> O. </PERSON> <PERSON> Perelman </PERSON>, who was in talks for a minority share in exchange for a large investment. <ORGANIZATION> Moody </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Investors </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> confirmed <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION>'s senior debt ratings after the plan was disclosed, removing a major threat to <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION>'s reputation and financial stability. Securities firms need good credit to borrow money for large transactions. <ORGANIZATION> Moody </ORGANIZATION>'s said the recapitalization plan `` will materially increase <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION>'s tangible net worth.'' `` Continuing efforts to reduce expenses should help boost <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION>'s performance,'' <ORGANIZATION> Moody </ORGANIZATION>'s said in a statement. `` However, intensifying competition in the global securities business and a difficult operating environment will remain constraints.'' The recapitalization includes the issue of 20 million new shares of <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION> common stock, which would raise $ 295 million if sold at Thursday's <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> closing price of $ 14.75 a share. <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Express </ORGANIZATION>, which bought its <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION> stake in 1981, would buy 3 million shares of the new issue, pumping about $ 44 million into <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION>. The travel, credit card and financial services company also plans to purchase <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION> cumulative preferred stock with a liquidation value of $ 250 million. In addition, $ 300 million in capital would be raised through two equal stock placements with large institutional investors. Finally, <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Express </ORGANIZATION> would buy <ORGANIZATION> Ayco </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, a <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION> financial counseling subsidiary, for $ 56 million, bringing the total new capital to $ 901 million. The institutional investors were not named, but Wall Street sources said discussions were held to give a minority stake in <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION> to <PERSON> Perelman </PERSON>. `` There were talks. They were preliminary. It really did n't come to terms,'' one source said. The sources, who asked not to be named, said <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Express </ORGANIZATION> had not finalized the outside investors, but they said there would be a number of them. The recapitalization is expected to shore up <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION>'s balance sheet but is not expected to guarantee a turnaround during a time of slumping profits and slow business on Wall Street. The plan would achieve <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Express </ORGANIZATION>' long-desired goal of reducing its stake in <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION> to under 50 percent from 61 percent to remove the brokerage's up-and-down performance from its earnings report. <ORGANIZATION> Moody </ORGANIZATION>'s on Oct. 30 said it was considering downgrading <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION>'s ratings on $ 4.8 billion in bonds and commercial paper because of the firm's low capital, weak profits and exposure in commercial real estate loans and investments, as well as the overall securities industry slump. <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION> stock has fallen in recent months because of poor earnings. The firm recently began laying off 800 workers to reduce its size to 35,700 employees, reshuffling its senior management and slashing stockbroker commissions for the first time in 15 years. The boards of directors of <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Express </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION> approved the recapitalization plan late Thursday. Under the plan, <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Express </ORGANIZATION> will remain the largest shareholder in <LOCATION> Shearson </LOCATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Nippon </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Life </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Insurance </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>, currently the second-largest shareholder with 13 percent, would remain in that position, although its new stake would be smaller. <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Express </ORGANIZATION> said it expects to record a one-time charge to net income reflecting the difference between the value of <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION> on its books and the value of its holdings based on the share price. The charge would total $ 60 million at Thursday's share price, <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Express </ORGANIZATION> said. Officials said <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION> was willing to part with Albany-based <ORGANIZATION> Ayco </ORGANIZATION>, which provides financial planning services to corporate executives, because it fits more with <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Express </ORGANIZATION>' operations. <ORG