 Stock prices slipped a notch today as the market absorbed the impact of the quarterly `` triple witching hour.'' The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials dropped 10.88 to 2,742.75 by noontime on Wall Street. Losers outnumbered gainers by about 7 to 5 in nationwide trading of <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> Exchange-listed issues, with 544 up, 788 down and 563 unchanged. Prices were buffeted around a bit by orders from professional traders engaged in computer-program strategies involving individual stocks and a series of expiring options and futures on stock indexes. The witching hour, which comes on the third Friday of the last month of each calendar quarter, did not appear to have more than a passing effect, however. Analysts said investors also seemed uncertain what to make of a spate of new government figures on the state of the economy. Reaction was mildly positive to news that the producer price index of finished goods dropped 0.1 percent in November. But a separate report showed a widening of the nation's trade deficit to $ 10.20 billion in October from a revised $ 8.51 billion the month before. Losers among the blue chips included <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motors </ORGANIZATION>, down \ at 43 \; <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Business </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Machines </ORGANIZATION>, down -RRB- at 94 -RCB-; <ORGANIZATION> DuPont </ORGANIZATION>, down -LCB- at 124 -LCB-, and <ORGANIZATION> USX </ORGANIZATION>, down -RRB- at 35 -RRB- <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> England </ORGANIZATION> tumbled 2 -RCB- to 9 | The company announced projected increases in its loan-loss reserve and non-performing assets, and said it would report a substantial loss for the year. The <ORGANIZATION> NYSE </ORGANIZATION>'s composite index of all its listed common stocks fell .57 to 193.40. At the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, the market value index was down .29 at 376.53. Volume on the <ORGANIZATION> Big </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> came to 123.01 million shares at noontime, up from 91.98 million at the same point Thursday.
