<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A midsession selloff sent stock prices lower today as the market was in the process of absorbing the impact of the quarterly `` triple witching hour.'' The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials, down more than 43 points at its afternoon low, was off 25.17 at 2,728.46 by 3 p.m. on Wall Street. Losers outnumbered gainers by more than 2 to 1 in nationwide trading of <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> Exchange-listed issues, with 467 up, 1,026 down and 487 unchanged. Analysts said a gradual early decline in prices picked up speed after stories crossed financial news wires that Gen. <PERSON> Manuel </PERSON> <PERSON> Antonio </PERSON> <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON> had been named chief of government in <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION> and was moving to confront a `` state of war'' arising from <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> policies. Brokers also noted cited pressure on financial stocks after the <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> England </ORGANIZATION> announced projected increases in its loan-loss reserve and non-performing assets, and said it would report a substantial loss for the year. Analysts said the news exacerbated recent worries about the real estate market in many parts of the country and the problems real-estate debt might pose should prices of properties lag for an extended period. <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> England </ORGANIZATION> shares led the active list, down 3 | at 8 -RCB- Federal National Mortgage, a market standout for most of 1989 until real estate-finance worries began to mount, dropped 1 -LCB- to 33 in active trading. Among the blue-chip industrials, <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Electric </ORGANIZATION> fell -RRB- to 64; <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motors </ORGANIZATION> 1 -LRB- to 42 -RRB-; <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Express </ORGANIZATION> | to 33 -LRB-, and <ORGANIZATION> Eastman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Kodak </ORGANIZATION> ~ to 40 | Prices were buffeted around a bit by orders from professional traders engaged in computer-program strategies involving individual stocks and a series of expiring options and futures on stock indexes. The so-called triple witching hour, which comes on the third Friday of the last month of each calendar quarter, did not appear to have more than a passing effect, however. The <ORGANIZATION> NYSE </ORGANIZATION>'s composite index of all its listed common stocks fell 1.61 to 192.36. At the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, the market value index was down 2.24 at 374.58. Volume on the <ORGANIZATION> Big </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> came to 195.34 million shares with an hour to go.
