<HEAD>Henley Group Split Into Two Companies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HAMPTON, N.H. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The board of directors of <ORGANIZATION> The </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Henley </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> on Friday approved splitting the conglomerate into two companies. The division continues a program that <PERSON> Henley </PERSON> has pursued of creating new publicly held companies. The two new companies are <ORGANIZATION> Henley </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Properties </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, specializing in real estate, and a new company called The <ORGANIZATION> Henley </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, which will hold all the remaining assets. `` Separating our extensive real-estate operations from <LOCATION> Henley </LOCATION>'s other businesses and investments continues our policy of grouping complementary assets in public companies so these assets can be better understood and evaluated by investors,'' said <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Dingman </PERSON>, chairman and chief executive officer of the existing conglomerate Stockholders will get one share of the new <ORGANIZATION> Henley </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION> as a tax-free distribution for each share they hold in the existing company as of Dec. 20. The remainder will be renamed <ORGANIZATION> Henley </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Properties </ORGANIZATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Henley </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Properties </ORGANIZATION>, with assets of $ 650 million, will own the existing company's real estate developments and acreage in southern <LOCATION> California </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Hawaii </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Wisconsin </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Michigan </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hampshire </LOCATION>. The new <ORGANIZATION> Henley </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> will own the existing company's remaining assets of about $ 3.5 billi