ON> <ORGANIZATION> Justice </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> in November to prohibit the Coors-Stroh transaction as anti-competitive. The department's antitrust division was reviewing the deal. Also pending is a federal lawsuit by <ORGANIZATION> S </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> P </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, a <LOCATION> Mill </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Valley </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Calif. </LOCATION>, company that owns several smaller breweries, including <ORGANIZATION> Pabst </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Blue </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ribbon </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hamms </ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON> Olympia </PERSON> and <PERSON> Falstaff </PERSON> and commands a 4 percent market share. The suit contends the combination would overwhelmingly increase the market share of the nation's four largest brewers.
