<HEAD>Bank of New England Announces Buildup of Loan Reserves, Corporate
Shakeup</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS 8th graf pv, `Bank of ...' to UPDATE with closing stock
price.</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JONATHAN YENKIN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A regional real estate slump prompted <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> England </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> to announce Friday it will sharply boost reserves against bad loans and that it expects a substantial loss for the year. The bank also announced it had reassigned a senior executive overseeing its real estate group, that it was considering the sale and merger of some operations and that it may rescind its common stock dividend declared Nov. 27. `` In my history of following bank stocks, that action is unprecedented,'' said <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Moynihan </PERSON>, senior vice president of <ORGANIZATION> Advest </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Boston </LOCATION>, referring to the stock move. `` I think what it tells you is the deterioration of the real estate market is getting faster. It goes from bad to worse every day.'' `` It may be in the best interest of the company to preserve its capital, even at the expense of shareholders,'' he said. <PERSON> Marcia </PERSON> <PERSON> Ryan </PERSON>, a spokeswoman for the bank, said a dividend of 34 cents a share had been declared for the fourth quarter ending Dec. 31. `` What we're saying is we're looking at a very large addition to our reserves and that is going to change the -LRB- dividend -RRB- calculations,'' she said. <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> England </ORGANIZATION>, which had a loan loss reserve of $ 354 million at the end of the third quarter, said it would boost that total to more than $ 1 billion in the current quarter. The company already had taken provisions for problem loans totaling about $ 207.3 million in the nine months ended Sept. 30. <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> E