eed regulatory minimums. <PERSON> Connolly </PERSON> also said the bank's senior management, along with a special committee of the board of directors, was addressing the company's loans and assets. Executive Vice President <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Sweeney </PERSON>, who had been head of the real estate group, has been removed from that position and assigned to other duties in the company. `` The finger has to point at someone,'' <PERSON> Moynihan </PERSON> said. `` These problems are real estate related. Some changes had to be made.'' The bank announced that Executive Vice President <PERSON> Hugh </PERSON> <PERSON> Taylor </PERSON>, head of the corporate banking group, will take over the real estate division until a permanent head is selected. <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> England </ORGANIZATION> also announced the special committee and management will look at steps to increase shareholder values, including possible mergers and sales of assets. The company posted a profit of $ 121.6 million in the nine months ended Sept. 30, down from $ 207.7 million in the same period a year earlier.
